narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's incredibly fulfilling and you will learn a tremendous amount of material with Fabi!!!
If you can take it with Fabi
Definitely! L2 is a lot of grammar, which can be tedious, but it it was a pretty drastic jump over the course of the semester in terms of comfort and speaking/reading ability.

Port L2 is not so hard! There is less stress to memorize vocab as there is in other language departments. The Portuguese program at Yale is more centered around increasing communication skills and sentence formation.
It is a very useful course, and after taking it it you should be ready to communicate in Portuguese if you do reasonably well.
I enjoyed this course. Fabi is a great teacher, and I felt that I learned a lot as a result. I would recommend this course to other students.
